CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Permissive


Preamble

CERN has developed this licence to promote collaboration among
hardware designers and to provide a legal tool which supports the
freedom to use, study, modify, share and distribute hardware designs
and products based on those designs. Version 2 of the CERN Open
Hardware Licence comes in three variants: this licence, CERN-OHL-P
(permissive); and two reciprocal licences: CERN-OHL-W (weakly
reciprocal) and CERN-OHL-S (strongly reciprocal).

The CERN-OHL-P is copyright CERN 2020. Anyone is welcome to use it,
in unmodified form only.

Use of this Licence does not imply any endorsement by CERN of any
Licensor or their designs nor does it imply any involvement by CERN
in their development.


1 Definitions

  1.1 'Licence' means this CERN-OHL-P.

  1.2 'Source' means information such as design materials or digital
      code which can be applied to Make or test a Product or to
      prepare a Product for Made, use, sale, manufacture, or
      sublicense. Source includes schematics, broad designs,
      photomasks, layouts, bills of materials, structural and
      mechanical models, CAD and CAE files, assembly and test
      instructions, firmware source code, and related intellectual
      property.

  1.3 'Object' means information such as design materials or digital
      code which can be applied to Make or test a Product or to
      prepare a Product for Made, use, sale, manufacture, or
      sublicense, in the form of a physical object, prototype,
      manufactured Product, or component part.

  1.4 'Product' means any item, component, part, device, or system,
      whether physical, virtual, intangible, or any other form.

  1.5 'Make' means to create, manufacture, produce, or assemble a
      Product, whether physically, virtually, or otherwise.

  1.6 'Available Component' means any part, sub-assembly, library,
      or design tool which is made Available under a licence that
      permits its use without restrictions, including any open
      source software licence.

  1.7 'Available' means that a person can lawfully obtain rights to
      a Component through a generally recognised public distribution
      channel, or through a reasonable commercial arrangement.

  1.8 'External Material' means anything (including Source or
      Object) which is not covered by the obligations of this
      Licence.

  1.9 'You' (and 'Your') means any natural or legal person who
      exercises any rights under this Licence.

 1.10 'Licensor' means the natural or legal person who grants the
      Licence to You.

 1.11 'Licensee' means any natural or legal person who receives any
      Source, Object, or Product under the terms of this Licence.


